 Eurasia. Ukraine’s soil water content was generally low, while northern China and eastern Russia’s values were higher; Global soil moisture in black soil had not changed significantly in the long-term series, and the overall trend was decreasing, largely due to changes in the northeast; Ukraine had the most stable dynamic change of soil moisture, while the Northeast Plain had relatively strong volatility; There is a possibility that soil moisture will decrease in the future due to the overall trend change in Eurasia. There may be a trend reversal in the 82.9\% area in the future, especially in Northeast China, which may be dominated by a decreasing trend. In general, the soil moisture content was higher than black soil in other parts of the world, but in the savannah ecosystem, the soil moisture content was higher than in any other part of the world. Conclusion: We obtained an international spatial and temporal distribution dataset for soil moisture in major blackland areas during 1990-2020 that will help to assess agricultural policy and ensure food security in the future.},
