	abstract = {Recently, soil moisture (SM) retrieval has become the first interest of the scientific community due to the increasing demand for water resources in several fields, especially the agricultural sector. A lack of such resources has been detected along with the increasing climate changes and disasters occurring such as drought. It has become very essential to search for efficient approaches and data sources that can serve effectively the SM retrieval goals. This paper is a literature review set to identify the strengths and weaknesses of the most relevant works in the area of SM retrieval and Remote Sensing (RS) published from 2017 to 2024. Summarizing the selected studies serves to detect the relevant information that tackles the SM retrieval challenges. Thus, creating new horizons for new research. One of the main fields of interest is SM retrieval over agriculture based on the synergistic use of Sentinel-1 (S-1) and Sentinel-2 (S-2) images. High accuracy has been achieved by combining different approaches such as backscattering models and Machine Learning (ML) algorithms (e.g., AIEM and NN algorithms). The application of such a combination is highly recommended due to its promising potential.},
